current15:24, 15 June 20215,184 × 3,456 (1 KB)Seloloving (talk | contribs)Fixed star and crescents in accordance with official construction sheet.
10:46, 24 December 20184,320 × 2,880 (1 KB)Jdx (talk | contribs)Fulfilling edit request by User:Tcfc2349.
06:11, 4 May 20104,320 × 2,880 (1 KB)Zscout370 (talk | contribs)Reverted to version as of 05:14, 4 May 2010 (nope, FOTW is not right, Pantone 032 is the legal shade)
05:38, 4 May 20104,320 × 2,880 (1 KB)Fry1989 (talk | contribs)Reverted to version as of 01:29, 4 May 2010 I requested the change based not only on FOTW but based on photos of the flag in use by Singapore government and military
05:14, 4 May 20104,320 × 2,880 (1 KB)Zscout370 (talk | contribs)Reverted to version as of 07:35, 10 January 2009 (nope; the SG government says Pantone 032 and honestly, a lot of the Pantone info on FOTW is not updated to current law)
01:29, 4 May 20104,320 × 2,880 (1 KB)McSush (talk | contribs)according http://flagspot.net/flags/sg.html "Pantone 186c" instead "Pantone 032" should be used...
07:35, 10 January 20094,320 × 2,880 (1 KB)Zscout370 (talk | contribs) I was emailed that the red is too pink, so going with official Pantone specs at http://www.pantone.com/pages/pantone/colorfinder.aspx?c_id=13050
09:03, 7 January 20094,320 × 2,880 (1 KB)Zscout370 (talk | contribs) I was asked to base my drawing from http://www.sg/explore/Singapore_Arms_And_Flag_And_National_Anthem_Rules.pdf, which I did. Only slight changes.
08:46, 5 December 20084,320 × 2,880 (1 KB)Zscout370 (talk | contribs) Reduced more code by using notepad, with great thanks to User:Fibonacci
